wikipedia_page.main: Thomas "Tom" Spence Tetley (birth registered second ¼ 1856 – 15 August 1924) was an English rugby union footballer who played in the 1870s. He played at representative level for England, and at club level for Bradford F.C., as a three-quarter, i.e. wing or centre. Prior to Tuesday 27 August 1895, Bradford F.C. was a rugby union club, it then became a rugby league club, and since 1907 it has been the association football (soccer) club Bradford Park Avenue.
